Auth0 Management API Python Test

Setup

Install the Python requests package before running the script:

```bash
python3 -m pip install requests
```

Run

Use one of the script commands:

```bash
python3 create_auth0_user.py create --email test@example.com --password TempPassword123!
python3 create_auth0_user.py update --user-id 'auth0|USER_ID_HERE' --nickname newnickname
python3 create_auth0_user.py delete --user-id 'auth0|USER_ID_HERE'
```

Keep quotes around Auth0 user IDs because they contain `|`, which your shell treats as a pipe.
